President Biden spoke at the International Brotherhood of Electrical Workers 103 in Boston, Massachusetts, expressing his gratitude for their support and emphasizing the importance of the upcoming Senate runoff election in Georgia. He praised Senator Warnock's character and highlighted the need for a 51st vote in the Senate to push forward their agenda. President Biden also discussed the significant investment in infrastructure and job creation, particularly in the field of semiconductors. He urged the union members to continue their efforts in mobilizing voters and emphasized the importance of preserving democracy. President Biden concluded by thanking the union for their contributions and urging them to keep up their work.